Package org.apache.heron.common.utils.metrics

Class FullSpoutMetrics

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.heron.common.utils.metrics.FullSpoutMetrics
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ComponentMetrics, ISpoutMetrics
    public class FullSpoutMetrics
extends java.lang.Object
implements ISpoutMetrics
    Spout's metrics to be collect We need to: 1. Define the metrics to be collected 2. New them in the constructor 3. Register them in registerMetrics(...) by using MetricsCollector's registerMetric(...) 4. Expose methods which could be called externally to change the value of metrics This is a spout metrics object with more information and it is used in heron core. To change to a faster metrics object, go to SpoutInstance.java and replace "new FullSpoutMetrcs" to "new SpoutMetrics"
